The MOOP aims to simultaneously minimise multiple objective functions that have conflicting natures. In this sense, it is impossible to obtain a single solution that can optimize all objective functions simultaneously. Hence, a set of solutions known as Pareto optimal set (POS) can be obtained. The MOOP can be defined as minimization as follows:2MinF(x)=f1(x),f2(x),...,fK(x)Tsubjecttox∈FS,FS=x|Gl(x)≤0,l=1,...,m,Hj(x)=0,j=m+1,....,M,lbi≤xi≤ubi,i=1,....,n\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
