Many meta-heuristic algorithms begin with an initial population, where the goodness of the initialization step can help generate better solutions in the final optimization iterations. Therefore, new ways for initializing the population of SCA have been incorporated with opposition-based learning (OBL) that was presented by Tizhoosh (Tizhoosh 2005), named as OBSCA (Abdelaziz et al. 2017). Based on this situation, the searching speed can be accelerated by retaining the fitter one opposite for an individual in the population.6xio=Lb+Ub-xi\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
