On the other hand, Gupta (Gupta and Deep 2019a) proposed a modified SCA (m-SCA) based on the OBL scheme to generate the opposite population to jump out from the local optima. In addition to OBL, a self-adaptive direction (SAD) is presented to exploit all the promising search regions. The SAD is combined with the classical updating rule of SCA, and the new updating solution is expressed as follows.7xi(t+1)=xi(t)+A1×sin(A2)×|A3xbest(t)-xi(t)|+SR(xcb-xi(t))r<0.5xi(t)+A1×cos(A2)×|A3xbest(t)-xi(t)|+SR(xcb-xi(t))r≥0.5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
